explanation: This solution uses dynamic programming to build a 2D table dp where dp[i][j] represents the minimum number of operations to transform the first i characters of word1 into the first j characters of word2. Then it backtracks from the bottom-right corner of the table to construct the lexicographically smallest valid sequence of indices.

